FT  16 AUG 93 / UK Company News: New London losses surge to Dollars 23.7m
Losses at New London, the UK oil and gas company, deepened from Dollars
1.46m to Dollars 23.7m (Pounds 15.9m) pre-tax in the year to March 31.
The London-based company booked net provisions of Dollars 16m against
disposals.
Turnover totalled Dollars 135.9m compared with Dollars 112.9m. Turnover of
the continuing operations amounted to Dollars 29.6m and generated operating
profits of Dollars 1.3m.
Losses per share widened from 1.2 cents to 23.2 cents.
